cast.overview: A chronicle of three weeks in the lives of several high school teachers, administrators and students through the eyes of substitute teacher, Henry Barthes. Henry roams from school to school, imparting modes of knowledge, but never staying long enough to form any semblance of sentient attachment.
cast.title: Detachment

details.biography: Kevin T. Collins is a native of native of the San Francisco Bay Area, where he spent his childhood and adolescence performing in various theaters. While he continues to work in work in theatre, Kevin's professional resume now includes several feature films, short films, and recurring and guest starring roles on TV series such as Law & Order and Law & Order: Criminal Intent. Kevin also works as a voice-over actor, recording audiobooks, animation work, radio and TV commercials, and more.
details.name: Kevin T. Collins
